The following files under public/js/engine/ are derived from MeshCommander:
  wsman-comm.js, wsman-stack.js, redirection.js, terminal.js, kvm.js, zlib.js,
  and the event-log / audit-log decoders and DMTF tables within amt-stack.js
  and amt-data.js.

The standalone MD5 implementation in public/js/engine/md5.js is a public-domain
implementation (Paul Johnston / Joseph Myers lineage), used in place of the
node-forge library that MeshCommander inlined.

Local modifications to the vendored engine:
  - kvm.js: the first framebuffer request after connect is non-incremental, and
    empty (0-tile) frames re-poll instead of stalling — so static screens such as
    BIOS/POST paint reliably (marked with "WebAMT:" comments).
  - kvm.js: mouse position is mapped with getBoundingClientRect()/clientX so the
    remote cursor tracks the pointer correctly under CSS scaling and scrolling.
  - redirection.js: Stop() records a disconnect code the viewer surfaces to the user.
  - wsman-comm.js / redirection.js: the relay WebSocket URLs were simplified for this
    browser-only relay (host is URL-encoded; the server-auth query flags were dropped).
  - wsman-stack.js / amt-stack.js / ider.js: the dead Node.js code paths (xmldom,
    atob, fs logging) and the browser-only environment detection were removed, since
    the engine now runs exclusively in the browser.
  - Unused stack methods, decoder tables and helper functions were pruned.

